Project Overview
The Simple Blogging Platform is a web-based application designed to provide a seamless experience for users to create, manage, and share their blog posts. This project serves as a foundational exercise in web development, focusing on utilizing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to build a functional and interactive platform.

Purpose
The platform aims to simulate a simplified blogging environment where users can express their thoughts and ideas through written content. By enabling users to create and manage their posts, the project highlights essential programming concepts and best practices in web development.

Features
User-friendly Interface:

The application is designed with a clean and intuitive layout, ensuring ease of use for all users.
Create Blog Posts:

Users can easily create new blog posts by filling out a simple form that includes fields for the title, content, and tags.
Display Posts:

All blog posts are displayed on the homepage in a list format, showcasing the title and a brief excerpt of the content, along with timestamps for each entry.
View Individual Posts:

When a user clicks on a post title, they are redirected to a dedicated page that presents the full content of the post.
Edit and Delete Functionality:

Users are able to edit existing posts (updating the title or content) and can delete posts they no longer wish to keep.
Data Persistence:

The application uses the browser's Local Storage to save blog posts, allowing them to persist even after the user refreshes or closes the page.
Responsive Design:

The platform is built to be mobile-friendly, providing an optimal viewing experience across various devices.
Learning Objectives
objectives:

Understand the fundamentals of web development and the relationship between HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Implement user interactions and manage data within the browser using Local Storage.
Develop skills in responsive design and user interface (UI) design principles.
Gain experience in project organization and structure, including file management and coding practices.